abstract: >
  Stellar Atlas is a detailed stellar evolution database generated using the MESA
  (Modules for Experiments in Stellar Astrophysics) code. It covers over 2350 simulations
  across a wide range of stellar masses (0.5 to 900 Mâ˜‰) and metallicities (Z = 0.0001 to 0.04),
  capturing hydrogen and helium exhaustion phases. The dataset includes HR diagrams,
  core diagnostic plots, ZAMS analysis, Gaia DR3 comparison, batch scripting tools, 
  and plotting utilities. Ideal for theoretical research, education, and code-based
  comparison with observational data.
